\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It is in this moment that Jesus draws a line in the sand and says there are two ways to live life, burdened down with a heavy weight and those who weight is light and easy to carry.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It\'92s as if He knew our culture and could peak into the future and see what we would be struggling with and says to us today\'85you don\'92t have to live that way.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 And throughout the text we have, there are instructions\'85on how to pull out the things we stress about and what to do when we feel empty\uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 And that is what I want to spend the rest of our time talking about\'85HOW do we stop ourselves from picking up the bricks of anxiety and stress and how to put down the ones we already have picked up.\uc0\u8232 \
